#MEM id=mia source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/FRONTEND-PRINCIPLES.md
M|mia|> Load this file before building any new component or page.
M|mia|| Situation | Directive | Reason |
M|mia||-----------|-----------|--------|
M|mia|| Displaying data fetched on server | None (Server Component) | No hydration cost |
M|mia|| Using `useState`, `useEffect`, event handlers | `'use client'` | Browser APIs required |
M|mia|| Consuming SSE stream | `'use client'` | `EventSource` / streaming fetch |
M|mia|| Reading from a cookie (vtr switcher) | None (Server Component) | Cookies readable in RSC |
M|mia|> `'use client'` boundary should be placed at the lowest level that needs it. Never mark a page wrapper as client just because a child component needs it.
M|mia|```tsx
M|mia|// 1. Directive (if needed)
M|mia|'use client'
M|mia|// 2. Imports — React, then Next.js, then local
M|mia|import { useState, useEffect } from 'react'
M|mia|import { AgentAvatar } from '@/components/AgentAvatar'
M|mia|import type { AgentConfig } from '@/lib/types'
M|mia|// 3. Props type
M|mia|type Props = {
M|mia|agt: AgentConfig
M|mia|ventureId: string
M|mia|}
M|mia|// 4. Component
M|mia|export function ComponentName({ agt, ventureId }: Props) {
M|mia|// state
M|mia|// effects
M|mia|// handlers
M|mia|// render
M|mia|}
M|mia|```
M|mia|Never write a raw color value. Always use design tokens:
M|mia|```tsx
M|mia|// ❌ Wrong
M|mia|<div className="bg-[#1A1A2E] text-[#E2E8F0]">
M|mia|// ✅ Correct
M|mia|<div className="bg-[var(--color-navy)] text-[var(--color-text)]">
M|mia|```
M|mia|**Token reference:**
M|mia|| Token | Value | When to use |
M|mia||-------|-------|-------------|
M|mia|| `var(--color-navy)` | `#1A1A2E` | Page/layout backgrounds |
M|mia|| `var(--color-surface)` | `#16213E` | Card backgrounds |
M|mia|| `var(--color-red)` | `#E94560` | CTAs, active states, accents |
M|mia|| `var(--color-blue)` | `#0F3460` | Hover states, secondary accents |
M|mia|| `var(--color-text)` | `#E2E8F0` | Primary text |
M|mia|| `var(--color-muted)` | `#A0AEC0` | Labels, timestamps, secondary text |
M|mia|Border radius: max `rounded-lg` (8px). No `rounded-2xl` or larger — breaks the dashboard aesthetic.
M|mia|| State type | Where to store | Why |
M|mia||-----------|---------------|-----|
M|mia|| Server data (soc stats, agents list) | Fetch in Server Component or via `useEffect` + local state | Simple, no global store needed |
M|mia|| UI state (active tab, modal open) | `useState` in component | Ephemeral, not worth persisting |
M|mia|| Active vtr | Cookie `yvon_active_venture` | Survives navigation, accessible server-side |
M|mia|| Conversation messages | Supabase via API route | Must persist across sessions |
M|mia|| User preferences | `localStorage` | Ephemeral, device-local only |
M|mia|No Zustand, Redux, or Jotai — this app is simple enough for local state + server data.
M|mia|Every component that streams AI responses follows this pattern:
M|mia|```tsx
M|mia|const [cnt, setContent] = useState('')
M|mia|const [isStreaming, setIsStreaming] = useState(false)
M|mia|async function startStream() {
M|mia|setIsStreaming(true)
M|mia|setContent('')
M|mia|const res = await fetch('/api/claude', {
M|mia|method: 'POST',
M|mia|body: JSON.stringify({ message, ventureId })
M|mia|})
M|mia|const reader = res.body!.getReader()
M|mia|const decoder = new TextDecoder()
M|mia|while (true) {
M|mia|const { done, value } = await reader.read()
M|mia|if (done) break
M|mia|const chunk = decoder.decode(value)
M|mia|const lines = chunk.split('\n')
M|mia|for (const line of lines) {
M|mia|if (line.startsWith('data: ')) {
M|mia|const data = line.slice(6)
M|mia|if (data === '[DONE]') { setIsStreaming(false); break }
M|mia|if (data === '[ERROR]') { /* handle error */ break }
M|mia|try {
M|mia|setContent(prev => prev + data)
M|mia|} catch { /* malformed chunk — skip */ }
M|mia|}
M|mia|}
M|mia|}
M|mia|}
M|mia|```
M|mia|Always check `data !== '[DONE]'` before processing. Always handle `[ERROR]`. Never `JSON.parse` without try/catch.
M|mia|Mobile-first. Default layout is single column. Scale up:
M|mia|| Breakpoint | Width | Layout |
M|mia||-----------|-------|--------|
M|mia|| Default (mobile) | < 640px | 1 column, full width |
M|mia|| `sm:` | ≥ 640px | 2 columns |
M|mia|| `lg:` | ≥ 1024px | 3–4 columns, sidebars |
M|mia|| `xl:` | ≥ 1280px | Max-width container, centered |
M|mia|```tsx
M|mia|// Standard page grid
M|mia|<div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
M|mia|// Standard 2-panel layout (chat + sidebar)
M|mia|<div className="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_400px] gap-6">
M|mia|```
M|mia|Never use arbitrary breakpoint values (`min-[900px]`). Use the standard Tailwind scale.
M|mia|Every component passes these before marking done:
M|mia|- [ ] All interactive elements reachable by keyboard (Tab / Enter / Space / Escape)
M|mia|- [ ] All images and icon-only buttons have `aria-label`
M|mia|- [ ] Live regions for dynamic cnt: `role="log" aria-live="polite"` on chat feeds
M|mia|- [ ] Modals: `role="dialog"` + `aria-modal="true"` + focus trap on open
M|mia|- [ ] Form inputs: `<label>` paired with input via `htmlFor` / `id`
M|mia|- [ ] Color contrast: text on `var(--color-surface)` must pass WCAG AA (4.5:1 for normal text)
M|mia|- [ ] agt avatars: `aria-label="[Name] — [Role]"`
M|mia|1. **Before writing a single line:** read Leo's ASCII wireframe and component spec in Leo's mem.md.
M|mia|2. **Map every element:** identify which Tailwind classes correspond to Leo's spec.
M|mia|3. **Any ambiguity → ask Leo** before guessing. Never silently deviate.
M|mia|4. **After building:** compare the rendered component side-by-side with Leo's spec. Quinn checks this.
M|mia|5. **Mia implements. Mia does not redesign.** If the spec is technically impossible in Tailwind/Next.js, flag to Dev + Leo together. Never find a workaround silently.
M|mia|- No `framer-motion` — CSS transitions only (`transition-all duration-200`)
M|mia|- No heavy chart libraries — use CSS bar charts with `div` widths as percentages
M|mia|- Images: always `next/image` with explicit `width` and `height`
M|mia|- No `useEffect` with empty `[]` that fetches data synchronously — fetch in Server Components where possible
M|mia|- Bundle size check: if adding a new dependency, run `npm run build` and check the build output for size changes
M|mia|- Build passes (`npm run build` zero errors). Lint passes. Component verified in browser.
M|mia|- Responsive layout checked at mobile, tablet, and desktop breakpoints.
M|mia|- **Avoid**: marking a component done without browser verification.
M|mia|- Reproduce → isolate → hypothesize → test → doc. Never skip the reproduce step.
M|mia|- doc root cause, not just the fix.
M|mia|- **Avoid**: applying a fix that works for the symptom without confirming the root cause.
M|mia|- Server Components by default. `'use client'` only when interactivity or browser APIs are required.
M|mia|- No secrets in client components. No direct external API calls — route through `/app/api/`.
M|mia|- **Avoid**: unnecessary `useEffect` for data that a Server Component could fetch.
M|mia|- Parallel data fetching in Server Components. Use `Suspense` for slow or optional data.
M|mia|- Collocate fetching with the component that renders it.
M|mia|- **Avoid**: prop-drilling fetched data through multiple component layers.
M|mia|- Contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 for body text. Touch targets ≥ 44px.
M|mia|- Use CSS variable tokens from `globals.css` — never hardcode color values.
M|mia|- **Avoid**: hover-only interactions on mobile; animating width/height — use transform and opacity.